<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
The genus is distinguished (together with 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Psilodercidae" genus="Thaiderces" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thaiderces" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Thaiderces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Li &amp; Li, 2017) from all the other genera in 
<taxonomicName family="Psilodercidae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="family">Psilodercidae</taxonomicName>
by the absence of an apical protrusion on the male cymbium. It is distinguished from the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Psilodercidae" genus="Thaiderces" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thaiderces" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Thaiderces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a single tooth on the cheliceral retromargin and the long embolus of the palpal bulb (
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, C" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Systematics" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="395 - 417" refId="B4" refString="Liu, C, Li, F, Li, S, Zheng, G, 2017. Five new genera of the subfamily Psilodercinae (Araneae: Ochyroceratidae) from Southeast Asia. Zoological Systematics 42: 395 - 417" title="Five new genera of the subfamily Psilodercinae (Araneae: Ochyroceratidae) from Southeast Asia." volume="42" year="2017">Liu et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Cheliceral promargin with lamina, retromargin with a tooth or denticle; palpal bulb with long embolus; conductor present or absent-if present, then embolus and conductor separated basally; female with two pairs of elongate, curved spermathecae (
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, C" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Systematics" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="395 - 417" refId="B4" refString="Liu, C, Li, F, Li, S, Zheng, G, 2017. Five new genera of the subfamily Psilodercinae (Araneae: Ochyroceratidae) from Southeast Asia. Zoological Systematics 42: 395 - 417" title="Five new genera of the subfamily Psilodercinae (Araneae: Ochyroceratidae) from Southeast Asia." volume="42" year="2017">Liu et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
